SUPPLEMENT TO THE BREWERS’ JOURNAL.

Breweries

IN THE

UNITED STATES.

January lst; 1899.

This DIRECTORY is an annual supplement to THE BREWERS’ JOURNAL, New York; subscription, $5 per annum.

CHANGES IN FIRM NAMES and NEW BREWERIES are published monthly in

The Brewers’ Journal,

New York—Ghicago—London.

Brewers of Lager Beer, Ale and Porter or Weiss Beer are designated by capital letters, as follows: Lager Beer, L; Ale and Porter, A; Weiss Beer, W.

Brewers who are also bottlers are designated by the capital letter B.

Brewers who have malt houses and make all or a part of the malt used by them are designated by a star (*).

Breweries that have been in operation less than one year are designated by a dagger (T). ,
